<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, bank deposits compete with =
a pile of $20 bills under your mattress. For most people in the US, most of=
 the time, bank accounts =E2=80=94=C2=A0which offer direct deposit, automat=
ic bill payments, probably higher security than your mattress, and maybe ev=
en interest =E2=80=94=C2=A0are more attractive than bills under the mattres=
s. But bills under the mattress have some advantages. There are=C2=A0<em>so=
me=C2=A0</em>contexts where you can spend them more easily than bank money;=
 some businesses only take cash and are not right next to an ATM. Plus if y=
ou are worried about your bank=E2=80=99s credit risk you might prefer the b=
ills.</p>
