<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A key metric of profitability for Indian banks=
, lending margins, is set to get a boost as the nation=E2=80=99s decision t=
o withdraw its highest-value currency note bolsters bank deposits.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Reserve Bank of India=E2=80=99s move to wi=
thdraw the 2,000 rupees ($24) notes will lead to growth in deposits at bank=
s and lower their cost of funds, according to a note from Axis Mutual Fund.=
 The step could boost deposits by as much as 2 trillion rupees through the =
end-September deadline to exchange the notes, the asset manager said. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As the rush to deposit the high-value currency=
 notes before the deadline gathers pace, banks=E2=80=99 margins could expan=
d, said Madan Sabnavis, chief economist at state-run Bank of Baroda.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the biggest banknote denomination=C2=A0is n=
o longer legal tender, then the pile of bills under your mattress has to ha=
ve more smaller-denomination=C2=A0bills, which makes the pile=C2=A0bigger, =
which makes your bed less comfortable, which makes the pile of bills under =
your mattress a less attractive competitor to bank=C2=A0deposits, which hel=
ps banks=E2=80=99 net interest margins.</p>
